Queenie Rosson https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Queenie_Rosson 0 Queenie Rosson (February 24, 1889 – December 19, 1978, West Palm Beach, Florida) was an early American silent film actress. She starred in 20 silent films films between 1914 and 1916 in films such as The Love Hermit working with actors such as Charlotte Burton and Harry von Meter.
